♪ THE ELVES ARE STRUMMING

02:42.205 --> 02:44.076
♪ RUDOLPH IS HUMMING ♪

02:44.816 --> 02:48.429
♪ SANTA IS ON HIS WAY

02:55.479 --> 02:57.960
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

03:18.198 --> 03:21.113
-[SCREAMS]

03:54.408 --> 03:55.322
-HELP!

03:59.456 --> 04:00.501
-ALL RIGHT.

04:00.631 --> 04:01.719
-C.J.: OKAY, WE GOT YOU.

04:01.850 --> 04:04.548
-MATT: ALL RIGHT, OKAY.

04:05.723 --> 04:08.770
-ALL RIGHT, COME
ON, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT.

04:09.988 --> 04:12.382
GONNA MAKE COMING DOWN THE
CHIMNEY A PIECE OF CAKE, HUH?

04:12.513 --> 04:14.210
-[LAUGHTER]

04:15.472 --> 04:16.473
ALL RIGHT, GOOD WORK, GUYS!

04:16.603 --> 04:18.214
ALL RIGHT, LET'S TAKE HIM IN.

04:20.956 --> 04:23.524
-MITCH: OKAY, EVEN
THOUGH WE ARE WELL INTO

04:23.654 --> 04:27.136
CHRISTMAS VACATION, AS YOU
CAN SEE, SUMMER WEATHER,

04:27.267 --> 04:29.791
WHICH MEANS YOU GOT
WORK CUT OUT FOR YOU.

04:29.921 --> 04:33.142
CHRISTMAS IN CALIFORNIA
MEANS GOING TO THE BEACH.

04:33.273 --> 04:35.187
ALL RIGHT, LET'S HIT IT!

04:35.318 --> 04:37.538
ONLY SEVEN SURFING DAYS
LEFT 'TIL CHRISTMAS.

04:38.930 --> 04:41.106
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
WITH ALL THIS STUFF?

04:42.760 --> 04:45.676
WE'RE GETTING SO MUCH
HERE, WHERE DO WE START?

04:46.373 --> 04:48.200
I GOT A LITTLE TINSEL
HERE, AND WHAT ELSE?

04:51.595 --> 04:54.119
AW, IS THAT A SIGH I DON'T HEAR?

04:55.947 --> 04:57.775
I KNOW, HONEY, I KNOW
YOU HAD YOUR HEART SET

04:57.906 --> 04:59.342
ON A WHITE CHRISTMAS
IN CONNECTICUT.

04:59.473 --> 05:01.170
-OH, MITCH, I KNOW
IT SOUNDS RIDICULOUS

05:01.301 --> 05:02.737
BUT I'VE NEVER HAD
A WHITE CHRISTMAS.

05:03.346 --> 05:05.261
I MEAN, MY PARENTS ALWAYS
MADE SURE WE HAD FUN

05:05.392 --> 05:08.220
AS KIDS BUT, CHRISTMAS WAS
ALWAYS ON THE BEACH AND

05:09.221 --> 05:12.834
I'VE ALWAYS WANTED TO THROW
SNOWBALLS AND GO SKIING

05:12.964 --> 05:16.054
DOWN A HILL ON A SLED
AND BUILD A SNOWMAN.

05:19.144 --> 05:21.321
WE THROW A PRETTY GOOD CHRISTMAS
AROUND HERE, DON'T WE, C.J.?

05:23.323 --> 05:25.107
-YEAH, THE BEST.
-SEE? THE BEST.

05:25.237 --> 05:27.414
-ESPECIALLY THIS YEAR BECAUSE
WE'VE ORGANIZED A CHRISTMAS

05:27.544 --> 05:29.372
DAY PICNIC AT THE BEACH
FOR HOMELESS CHILDREN

05:29.503 --> 05:31.679
AND WE HAVE A PRIEST FROM
ST. FRANCIS COMING WITH

05:31.809 --> 05:33.158
A BUNCH OF KIDS AND
THEY'RE GONNA DECORATE

05:33.289 --> 05:34.203
THE CHRISTMAS TREE
AT THE HEADQUARTERS.

05:34.334 --> 05:36.248
-AH, C.J., THAT SOUNDS TERRIFIC!

05:36.379 --> 05:38.729
BUT IT'S JUST THAT, THIS
IS PROBABLY GONNA BE

05:38.860 --> 05:40.165
MY LAST CHANCE AT
A WHITE CHRISTMAS.

05:40.296 --> 05:42.603
-DON'T BE SILLY,
THERE'LL BE OTHER YEARS!

05:45.388 --> 05:47.956
C.J.! WE HAVEN'T GOT MUCH TIME

05:48.086 --> 05:50.654
TO GET THIS GIRL IN
THE CHRISTMAS SPIRIT!

05:51.699 --> 05:53.048
-WELL THEN, WE BETTER START
GETTING HER IN THE MOOD.

05:53.788 --> 05:55.833
WE HAVE TREES TO DECORATE.

05:56.399 --> 05:58.401
-POPCORN AND
CRANBERRIES TO STRING.

05:58.923 --> 05:59.707
-COOKIES TO BAKE.

05:59.837 --> 06:01.099
-AND CAROLS TO SING.

06:01.230 --> 06:02.231
-WE'RE SWAMPED.

06:02.840 --> 06:06.278
-NOW, THIS MAY
NOT BE CONNECTICUT,

06:07.018 --> 06:08.324
AND I CAN'T PROMISE YOU SNOW,

06:09.630 --> 06:12.372
BUT I CAN PROMISE
YOU A CHRISTMAS

06:12.981 --> 06:15.287
YOU WILL NEVER FORGET.

06:22.512 --> 06:23.818
-MATT, IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

06:25.167 --> 06:26.037
-YEAH.

06:27.952 --> 06:29.214
I JUST DIDN'T FEEL
LIKE STANDING AROUND

06:29.345 --> 06:30.651
AND COMPARING
CHRISTMAS MEMORIES.

06:31.391 --> 06:32.261
-WHY NOT?

06:34.132 --> 06:35.177
-CAUSE I DON'T HAVE ANY.

06:43.098 --> 06:45.361
-[CROWD CHATTERING]

06:53.848 --> 06:55.066
-SID: UH-HUH?

06:57.547 --> 06:59.157
YEAH, KUBLA KHAN
IS GONNA WIN BIG

06:59.288 --> 07:00.985
AND YOU'RE GONNA FINALLY
GET YOURSELF OUT OF DEBT.

07:01.116 --> 07:02.117
THE BET IS ON!

07:05.207 --> 07:09.559
AND WHEN HE DOESN'T WIN,
FINALLY LOSE YOUR HOUSE TO ME.

07:11.300 --> 07:15.304
[LAUGHS] OH KYLA...

07:16.348 --> 07:18.394
YOU'RE INTO ME NOW
FOR TEN GRAND, BABY,

07:18.525 --> 07:21.223
I'VE GIVEN YOU ALL THE
LEEWAY I CAN, I UH...

07:23.530 --> 07:24.618
I NEED TO COLLECT.

07:25.836 --> 07:28.709
-COME ON, SID,
JUST ONE MORE BET?

07:30.624 --> 07:32.190
I KNOW THIS HORSE'LL COME IN.

07:33.975 --> 07:37.108
TELL YOU WHAT, WHY DON'T WE
JUST DISCUSS THIS OVER LUNCH.

07:40.329 --> 07:41.199
MY TREAT.

07:42.592 --> 07:43.767
-WELL...

07:46.204 --> 07:48.032
THAT'S AN OFFER I
JUST CAN'T REFUSE.

08:02.438 --> 08:03.308
SHALL WE?

08:08.749 --> 08:10.881
-LOOK AT THE TREES, SID!

08:13.275 --> 08:14.145
HI, SANTA.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.147
-SANTA: MERRY CHRISTMAS!

08:19.760 --> 08:21.936
-HEY! HEY! THAT'S MY PURSE!

08:23.024 --> 08:24.939
SID, EVERYTHING I HAVE IS IN
THAT BAG, YOU GOTTA GET HIM!

08:25.069 --> 08:28.159
-HEY! HEY, STOP THAT
KID! GET BACK HERE!

08:28.290 --> 08:30.118
HEY! HEY! GET BACK HERE!

08:30.248 --> 08:31.554
THAT BOY'S A THIEF!
GET BACK HERE!

08:31.685 --> 08:35.123
-HEY! HEY! STOP! STOP
RIGHT NOW! HEY!

08:48.440 --> 08:51.052
-[BREATHING HARD]

09:00.061 --> 09:00.931
MY KEYS!

09:01.802 --> 09:04.979
THE LITTLE WITCH STOLE MY KEYS!
GAH! OH!

09:06.154 --> 09:07.198
-YES!

09:22.170 --> 09:23.563
-DAMN MANIPULATIVE LITTLE--

09:30.874 --> 09:32.789
YEAH, TONY, THIS IS SID.

09:33.660 --> 09:36.184
LISTEN, I GOT A JOB FOR YOU.

09:46.629 --> 09:47.630
-GOTCHA!

09:48.718 --> 09:51.112
-MOM! YOU SCARED ME TO DEATH!

09:51.242 --> 09:52.722
-I'M SORRY, KIDDO!

09:53.418 --> 09:55.812
WE MADE A HUGE HAUL OFF THAT

09:55.943 --> 09:58.815
OLD GEEZER, $10,000.

09:58.946 --> 10:00.425
ANYWAY, HE'S BEEN
CHEATING US FOR MONTHS

10:00.556 --> 10:01.601
SO I FIGURED HE OWES US.

10:02.514 --> 10:04.778
-MOM, YOU KNOW WE HUSTLED HIM.

10:05.605 --> 10:09.652
-YES, WE DID!
[LAUGHS] ALL RIGHT!

10:09.783 --> 10:11.959
-[EXCITED CHATTER]

10:31.848 --> 10:32.806
-HI!

10:33.763 --> 10:36.810
I PICKED THIS SPOT ESPECIALLY
TO BE NEAR YOU, A LIFEGUARD.

10:37.549 --> 10:39.203
MY COLLEAGUES AND I
ARE HERE ON VACATION.

10:39.334 --> 10:40.944
MY NAME IS BENJAMIN, BUT
YOU CAN CALL ME BENNY.

10:41.075 --> 10:42.598
-BENNY, IT'S NICE TO
MEET YOU, MY NAME'S MATT.

10:42.729 --> 10:43.686
-NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:44.861 --> 10:46.950
WE ALL REALLY
NEEDED SOME TIME OFF

10:47.081 --> 10:49.649
AND WE DECIDED SUNNY
CALIFORNIA'S THE PLACE TO BE.

10:49.779 --> 10:50.911
-IS THIS YOUR
FIRST TIME OUT HERE?

10:51.738 --> 10:54.436
-WELL, WE'VE...FLOWN
OVER THE AREA.

10:55.306 --> 10:58.658
IT'S BEAUTIFUL HERE, IT'S
FREEZING WHERE WE COME FROM.

10:59.528 --> 11:01.051
-MATT: WELL, WHERE YOU FROM?
-DEBBIE: BENNY!

11:02.313 --> 11:03.793
DON'T KEEP BOTHERING
THE LIFEGUARD!

11:03.924 --> 11:05.273
HE DOESN'T WANNA
HEAR YOU RAMBLE ON.

11:05.403 --> 11:07.014
LET'S GET OUTTA HERE!

11:08.624 --> 11:10.713
COME ON GUYS, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING, SPROUTING ROOTS?

11:10.844 --> 11:12.541
WHO WANTS TO GO FOR A SWIM?

11:12.672 --> 11:14.195
OKAY, GUYS, LET'S HIT THE WATER!

11:14.325 --> 11:16.371
-[ALL CHEERING]

11:39.916 --> 11:42.266
-C.J.: COME ON, GUYS,
RIGHT OVER HERE.

11:43.615 --> 11:44.616
COME ON GUYS!

11:45.966 --> 11:47.576
OKAY EVERYBODY, LISTEN UP!

11:47.707 --> 11:49.578
YOU'RE GONNA RUN TO THE
JETTY AND THEN YOU'RE GONNA

11:49.709 --> 11:51.841
GO TO HEADQUARTERS TO DECORATE
THE CHRISTMAS TREE, OKAY?

11:51.972 --> 11:52.842
-ALL: YEAH!

11:53.669 --> 11:54.844
-[LAUGHS]

11:54.975 --> 11:57.934
-READY? ON YOUR
MARK, GET SET, GO!

12:01.372 --> 12:02.591
-YOU'RE TERRIFIC WITH THE KIDS.

12:02.722 --> 12:05.072
-THANKS! BELIEVE
ME, IT'S NOT HARD.

12:05.202 --> 12:06.943
-I BELIEVE YOU, I SPEND
QUITE A BIT OF TIME WITH THEM.

12:07.074 --> 12:09.424
I'M FATHER SAM RYAN,
YOU MUST BE C.J. PARKER.

12:09.554 --> 12:12.035
-YEAH, I AM. [LAUGHS]

12:12.166 --> 12:15.691
I JUST DIDN'T EXPECT, UM-- DON'T
YOU WEAR THE-- THE LITTLE--

12:15.822 --> 12:17.475
-YOU MEAN THE
FUNNY LITTLE COLLAR.

12:17.606 --> 12:20.000
MY PARISHIONERS GET QUITE UPSET
IF THEY SEE ME WITHOUT IT.

12:20.130 --> 12:21.741
THEY FIGURE IF I HAVEN'T GOT
IT ON, I MUST BE HAVING FUN.

12:21.871 --> 12:23.568
-WELL, I DON'T MIND.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.614
ACTUALLY, YOU'D PROBABLY GET
THE LITTLE FUNNY TAN LINE.

12:27.268 --> 12:29.574
-YOU KNOW, UH, WE'RE ACTUALLY
IN THE SAME LINE OF WORK.

12:29.705 --> 12:31.011
WE BOTH SAVE LIVES.

12:31.881 --> 12:33.361
-YOU JUST TAKE THEM A
LITTLE CLOSER TO HEAVEN.

12:33.491 --> 12:35.406
-YOU KEEP THEM FROM
GETTING THERE TOO SOON.

12:36.973 --> 12:39.236
I'M GLAD WE'RE GONNA BE
WORKING TOGETHER, C.J.

12:39.367 --> 12:41.412
AND PLEASE, CALL ME SAM.

12:42.326 --> 12:44.676
-OKAY, SAM, LET'S
GET TO HEADQUARTERS.

12:44.807 --> 12:45.721
-LET'S GO.

12:50.726 --> 12:53.642
-I'M TELLING YOU, JOEY, THERE'S
A SUCKER BORN EVERY MINUTE.

12:54.817 --> 12:56.906
AND THEY'RE JUST PARADING
RIGHT IN FRONT OF US.

12:57.037 --> 12:59.822
-WELL, I SAY WE HAVE
ENOUGH MONEY FOR AWHILE.

12:59.953 --> 13:02.607
I THINK WE OUGHT TO JUST,
YOU KNOW, RELAX AND SPEND IT.

13:03.521 --> 13:06.089
-THIS IS THE TIME TO MAKE
MONEY, HONEY, WHEN WE GOT IT!

13:06.220 --> 13:07.743
NOW YOU KNOW WHAT
TO DO, DON'T YOU?

13:08.309 --> 13:09.614
-I THINK I'VE SEEN
PAPER MOON ENOUGH TIMES.

13:09.745 --> 13:11.181
I THINK I CAN HANDLE IT.

13:11.312 --> 13:12.400
-THAT'S MY KID!

13:15.272 --> 13:16.839
-[CROWD CHATTERING]

13:30.200 --> 13:31.811
-HI.
-HI, HOW ARE YOU?

13:31.941 --> 13:33.203
-GOOD.
-GOOD.

13:33.334 --> 13:36.293
-UM I'LL TAKE THESE.

13:36.424 --> 13:38.295
-OKAY, WANT ME TO
WRAP THEM UP FOR YOU?

13:38.426 --> 13:39.906
-NO, I THINK I'LL WHERE THEM.

13:40.036 --> 13:41.342
-OKAY.
-CHANGE FOR A HUNDRED?

13:43.344 --> 13:44.562
HOW DO THEY LOOK?

13:44.693 --> 13:46.390
-THEY LOOK GOOD ON YOU.
-THANK YOU.

13:46.521 --> 13:48.610
-YOU'RE WELCOME.
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

13:58.489 --> 14:00.100
-MERRY CHRISTMAS, OFFICER.

14:00.230 --> 14:02.319
-AND TO YOU, SANTA,
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

14:03.277 --> 14:06.541
-HI, CAN I HELP
YOU WITH ANYTHING?

14:06.671 --> 14:08.282
-YES, I'D LIKE
TO GET THIS RING.

14:08.412 --> 14:09.457
-OKAY.

14:10.588 --> 14:12.199
-IT'S FOR MY MOM'S BIRTHDAY.

14:12.329 --> 14:13.765
IT'S GONNA LOOK REAL RAD ON HER.

14:13.896 --> 14:16.072
-OKAY, THAT'LL BE FIVE DOLLARS.

14:20.076 --> 14:21.425
IT'S PRETTY, SHE'LL LIKE IT.

14:26.343 --> 14:27.214
THANK YOU.

14:31.305 --> 14:32.784
OKAY, THERE YOU GO.

14:33.437 --> 14:34.395
-THANK YOU.

14:34.525 --> 14:36.005
-YOU'RE WELCOME, BYE BYE.

14:37.137 --> 14:39.966
-HEY, WAIT A MINUTE, CAN I HAVE
THE REST OF MY CHANGE PLEASE?

14:40.096 --> 14:41.924
-I GAVE YOU ALL
YOUR CHANGE, HONEY.

14:42.055 --> 14:43.360
-I GAVE YOU A
HUNDRED DOLLAR BILL.

14:44.187 --> 14:45.710
-SWEETIE, NO YOU DIDN'T,
YOU GAVE ME A TEN.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.582
-I GAVE YOU A
HUNDRED DOLLAR BILL!

14:47.712 --> 14:50.802
IT HAD MY NAME ON IT, IT
SAID, "HAPPY BIRTHDAY, JOEY"!

14:50.933 --> 14:52.369
-OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

14:52.500 --> 14:54.763
-JUST LOOK!
-OKAY, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.

15:00.508 --> 15:03.641
OH MY GOD, KID, LOOK
I'M REALLY SORRY.

15:03.772 --> 15:05.687
HERE, I'LL TELL YOU
WHAT, YOU JUST TAKE THAT

15:05.817 --> 15:07.384
AND DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, OKAY?

15:13.956 --> 15:15.697
-GOOD JOB!

15:19.962 --> 15:23.009
-HEY! HEY! POLICE! STOP!

15:23.139 --> 15:24.358
THAT KID STOLE MY MONEY!

15:24.488 --> 15:25.663
-TAKE THE MONEY AND RUN.

15:25.794 --> 15:26.926
RUN, JOEY, RUN!

15:27.578 --> 15:29.015
-HEY, HEY, COME HERE! HEY!

15:29.145 --> 15:30.668
-HEY, LET ME GO!

15:39.025 --> 15:40.548
-SHE CONNED ME OUT OF
ALMOST $100.

15:40.678 --> 15:42.115
-PROVE IT.

15:42.245 --> 15:43.812
-I WOULD BUT YOUR BOY
TOOK OFF WITH MY MONEY!

15:44.508 --> 15:45.945
-WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO TAKE THIS
DOWN TO THE STATION, FOLKS.

15:46.075 --> 15:46.946
LET'S GO.

15:48.164 --> 15:49.513
-BENNY: HEY, MATT, HOBIE!

15:49.644 --> 15:51.428
-HEY.
-HEY, BENNY, WHAT'S UP?

15:51.559 --> 15:54.605
-MY AGE AND SHAQUILLE O'NEAL,
HAVE YOU SEEN THAT GUY?

15:54.736 --> 15:57.043
-[LAUGHTER]

15:57.173 --> 15:58.566
-SO, YOU GUYS
HAVING A GOOD TIME?

16:00.307 --> 16:01.177
-NO.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.486
-WE'RE HAVING A GREAT TIME!

16:06.443 --> 16:07.575
THE OLD GEEZER WE WORK FOR IS A

16:07.705 --> 16:09.055
SLEIGH DRIVER THIS TIME OF YEAR.

16:09.620 --> 16:11.013
-"SLEIGH" DRIVER?

16:11.927 --> 16:13.015
-DID I SAY SLEIGH DRIVER?

16:13.146 --> 16:14.538
I MEANT SLAVE DRIVER.

16:14.669 --> 16:17.585
FACT IS, WE TOOK OFF
WITHOUT TELLING HIM,

16:17.715 --> 16:20.283
SO WE'RE TRYING TO
KEEP A LOW PROFILE,

16:20.414 --> 16:22.851
UH, LOWER PROFILE, ANYWAY.

16:22.982 --> 16:24.940
-SO WHAT KIND OF
WORK DO YOU GUYS DO?

16:25.071 --> 16:27.290
-YOU GUYS'LL HAVE TO
FORGIVE HIM, IF YOU GIVE HIM

16:27.421 --> 16:30.206
THE CHANCE, HE WILL TALK
FOREVER ABOUT ANYTHING.

16:31.294 --> 16:32.295
WHO WANTS TO PLAY FRISBEE?

16:37.474 --> 16:39.999
-I'D LIKE TO TELL YOU WHAT
WE DO, BUT IT'S TOP SECRET.

16:41.652 --> 16:44.003
BESIDES, YOU WOULDN'T
BELIEVE ME IF I TOLD YOU!

16:59.322 --> 17:01.890
-TONY, THAT'S HIM,
THAT'S THE KID, GET HIM!

17:02.021 --> 17:03.631
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU DO
JUST GET MY MONEY BACK.

17:03.761 --> 17:05.459
GET HIM! GO, GO!

17:08.810 --> 17:10.290
-TONY: HEY! COME HERE, KID!

17:10.420 --> 17:13.510
-DON'T LET HIM GET
AWAY! GET HIM, GET HIM!

17:13.641 --> 17:15.859
-COME HERE, COME HERE, YOU!

17:15.991 --> 17:18.037
DON'T MAKE ME CHASE YOU!

17:18.166 --> 17:20.213
-[CHEERING]

17:24.260 --> 17:27.349
-HEY, HOBE, YOU STILL
BELIEVE IN SANTA CLAUSE?

17:28.089 --> 17:29.004
-YOU SERIOUS?

17:34.140 --> 17:36.794
-COME HERE, COME HERE, YOU!

17:37.621 --> 17:38.709
I GOTCHA NOW!

17:40.146 --> 17:41.147
COME HERE!

17:48.197 --> 17:50.330
COME HERE! COME HERE! [LAUGHS]

17:50.460 --> 17:51.940
COME HERE, COME HERE!

17:52.071 --> 17:54.334
NOT THIS TIME! NOT THIS TIME!

17:54.464 --> 17:55.465
WHERE'S YOUR MOTHER?

17:55.596 --> 17:58.642
WHERE'S YOUR MOTHER, KID? OW!

17:59.687 --> 18:01.384
LISTEN, WE JUST WANT THE MONEY.

18:01.515 --> 18:03.256
-LET ME GO, YOU BIG FAT LUMMOX!

18:03.386 --> 18:04.474
-LOOK, WE JUST WANT THE MONEY.

18:04.605 --> 18:06.781
-JOEY: HELP! HELP!

18:07.390 --> 18:08.957
-WHERE'S THE MONEY? OW!

18:09.088 --> 18:10.741
WHERE'D YOU LEARN THAT?

18:11.394 --> 18:14.267
-HELP, SOMEBODY, HELP!

18:15.920 --> 18:17.922
LIFEGUARD!
-LIFEGUARD?

18:18.532 --> 18:19.533
I'LL FIND YOU AGAIN, KID.

18:19.663 --> 18:20.838
-MATT: GET AWAY FROM HIM!

18:25.104 --> 18:27.236
-THAT BUM TRIED TO
STEAL MY FIVE DOLLARS!

18:27.367 --> 18:28.585
IT'S ALL I GOT!

18:29.108 --> 18:30.152
-IT'S OKAY.

18:34.461 --> 18:37.768
-[COUGHING AND SPLUTTERING]

18:37.899 --> 18:39.901
-[ALL YELLING]

18:46.212 --> 18:48.779
-MATT! MATT, IT'S BENNY!

18:48.910 --> 18:51.086
-HOBIE, TAKE HIM
BACK TO HEADQUARTERS.

18:54.133 --> 18:56.178
-DON'T WORRY, I WON'T LET
ANYTHING HAPPEN TO YOU.

19:00.008 --> 19:01.705
-[ALL YELLING]

19:43.443 --> 19:45.227
[CHEERING]

19:59.807 --> 20:02.375
-YOU'RE ALL RIGHT, BENNY.
-[ALL CHATTERING]

20:06.030 --> 20:06.988
-YOU OKAY, BENNY?

20:10.557 --> 20:12.036
YOU OKAY?

20:12.776 --> 20:15.475
WE'RE TRYING TO GO UNNOTICED
HERE, BENNY, NOT MAKE
THE HEADLINES.

20:16.867 --> 20:20.044
-I'M SORRY, DEBBIE, I DIDN'T
REALIZE I WAS SO OUT OF SHAPE.

20:20.915 --> 20:23.222
I USED TO SWIM EVERY DAY BEFORE
I STARTED WORKING FOR KRIS.

20:27.138 --> 20:29.663
-I JUST WANNA MAKE SURE
HE'S BREATHING OKAY.

20:29.793 --> 20:31.491
YOU'RE BREATHING
OKAY NOW, RIGHT, BEN?

20:35.103 --> 20:36.713
I THINK HE'S JUST FINE.

20:38.498 --> 20:39.760
UM, YOU CAN GO NOW.

20:44.765 --> 20:46.593
-YOU GUYS WORK FOR SANTA
AT THE MALL OR SOMETHING?

20:47.637 --> 20:50.074
-WE GOTTA GO. SEE YA.
THANKS A LOT.

21:08.571 --> 21:12.271
-UH, HI, DAD. TRACY.

21:12.401 --> 21:15.143
-I THOUGHT YOU WERE SPENDING
THE NIGHT AT LANDON'S.

21:15.752 --> 21:19.365
-SOMETHING CAME UP,
HOLD ON, COME HERE.

21:20.757 --> 21:21.671
DAD...

21:24.021 --> 21:26.981
THIS IS JOEY JENNINGS.

21:27.764 --> 21:29.331
HE GOT ON THE WRONG
BUS TO SAN DIEGO.

21:29.462 --> 21:31.115
HIS MOM'S GONNA PICK
HIM UP TOMORROW.

21:31.855 --> 21:33.509
HE JUST NEEDS A
PLACE TO STAY SO--

21:34.510 --> 21:37.861
-[LAUGHS] HERE? TONIGHT?

21:40.037 --> 21:43.214
HI, I'D REALLY LIKE
TO TALK TO YOUR MOM.

21:43.345 --> 21:45.956
-I TALKED TO HER, BUT YOU
WON'T BE ABLE TO REACH HER

21:46.087 --> 21:47.871
CAUSE SHE'S ON THE BUS.

21:48.002 --> 21:50.309
-WELL, I THINK I'LL LEAVE
YOU FELLAS TO YOUR MAN STUFF.

21:50.439 --> 21:53.877
-AH, UM [MUTTERS]

21:54.443 --> 21:57.228
-AND I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW
MORNING BRIGHT AND EARLY.

22:02.277 --> 22:03.191
-NIGHT.

22:09.763 --> 22:10.590
-JOEY: THANKS.

22:14.115 --> 22:16.900
-IT'S...BATH TIME.

22:17.901 --> 22:19.816
THANK YOU, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

22:23.951 --> 22:25.735
-WHERE'D YOU FIND
THIS KID, ANYWAY?

22:27.563 --> 22:29.260
YOU ALL RIGHT?
-JOEY: YEAH.

22:35.876 --> 22:39.009
-WAIT A MINUTE, YOU
DIDN'T TAKE A SHOWER.

22:39.140 --> 22:40.533
YOU JUST TURNED THE WATER ON.

22:41.403 --> 22:42.839
-I DIDN'T FEEL
LIKE GETTING WET.

22:42.970 --> 22:44.580
-YEAH-- WHOA THERE PARTNER,
I THINK MAYBE

22:44.711 --> 22:45.973
WE'LL GO IN TOGETHER THIS TIME.

22:46.103 --> 22:47.409
-I DON'T THINK SO.

22:48.149 --> 22:49.019
-WHY NOT?

22:53.981 --> 22:54.938
-[WHISPERS] I'M REALLY
A LITTLE GIRL.

22:55.069 --> 22:57.811
-[LAUGHING] WHY CAN'T YOU--

22:59.813 --> 23:00.727
-HE...

23:02.859 --> 23:03.686
IS A SHE.

23:05.514 --> 23:07.124
-HOBIE: NO WAY!

23:12.042 --> 23:14.436
-[CHATTERING]

23:27.101 --> 23:31.279
-HMM, I'D KNOW THOSE
HANDS, THAT SCENT ANYWHERE.

23:31.888 --> 23:32.759
JOSEPH?

23:32.889 --> 23:34.630
-JOSEPH! WHO'S JOSEPH?

23:35.979 --> 23:38.504
-HE'S JUST A REPRESENTATIVE
OF ALL THE MEN IN THE WORLD

23:38.634 --> 23:40.810
WHO COULD NEVER HOLD
A CANDLE TO YOU.

23:43.465 --> 23:44.423
WHERE'S HOBIE?

23:44.553 --> 23:46.381
-HOBIE IS BABYSITTING JOEY.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.514
-OH, AND HOW'D THINGS
GO WITH HIM LAST NIGHT?

23:48.644 --> 23:49.602
-HIM IS A HER.

23:50.254 --> 23:51.517
-WHAT?

23:51.647 --> 23:53.083
-YEAH, TURNS OUT
JOEY IS A LITTLE GIRL.

23:53.606 --> 23:56.347
-[LAUGHS] A GIRL?
HOW'D YOU FIND OUT?

24:05.531 --> 24:07.141
-WOW, THAT'S TERRIFIC!

24:08.011 --> 24:09.752
YOU GUYS BEEN AT THIS
FOR TWO DAYS NOW.

24:09.883 --> 24:11.624
-YEAH, WE'RE ALMOST
OUT OF ORNAMENTS.

24:11.754 --> 24:12.842
-NOT A MOMENT TOO SOON.

24:12.973 --> 24:15.758
-GARNER: HO, HO, HO!

24:16.977 --> 24:21.111
MERRY CHRISTMAS! [LAUGHING]

24:23.374 --> 24:24.724
-GARNER, IS THAT YOU IN THERE?

24:26.116 --> 24:28.423
-OF COURSE, IT'S ME, EXHAUSTED.

24:28.554 --> 24:30.860
I MUST HAVE HAD 100 KIDS
ON MY LAP TODAY.

24:31.992 --> 24:34.081
-I'VE NEVER SEEN YOU SO
FESTIVE, I MEAN, YOU'RE

24:34.211 --> 24:36.257
USUALLY QUITE CYNICAL
THIS TIME OF YEAR.

24:36.387 --> 24:37.650
-WELL, LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING, PARTNER,
I'VE MISSED MY CALLING

24:37.780 --> 24:39.042
I'M FAKING IT, I
SHOULD BE AN ACTOR.

24:39.565 --> 24:41.480
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING?
YEAH, BUT, YOU KNOW,

24:41.610 --> 24:43.046
I FIGURE IF I CAN
CONVINCE OTHERS,

24:43.177 --> 24:44.570
MAYBE I CAN CONVINCE MYSELF.

24:45.179 --> 24:47.050
HO, HO, HO!

24:47.181 --> 24:48.791
-HI, DAD. HI, GARNER.

24:49.400 --> 24:50.489
-SO MUCH FOR CONVINCING OTHERS.

24:51.925 --> 24:54.188
-HEY, JOEY, YOU WANT
TO TALK TO SANTA

24:54.318 --> 24:55.406
AND TELL HIM WHAT YOU
WANT FOR CHRISTMAS?

24:55.929 --> 24:57.321
-THERE'S NO SUCH
THING AS SANTA.

24:57.452 --> 24:59.628
THAT'S JUST A FAIRY
TALE ADULTS MAKE UP

24:59.759 --> 25:01.238
TO MAKE THEIR KIDS
BEHAVE ALL YEAR.

25:04.067 --> 25:05.547
-[SPUTTERS]

25:11.510 --> 25:14.730
-HO, HO, HO, WHAT
A LOVELY TREE.

25:14.861 --> 25:15.905
LET'S GO LOOK AT THE TREE.

25:20.693 --> 25:22.956
-SAY, JUNIOR
LIFEGUARDS, COME ON!

25:23.086 --> 25:25.349
THE KIDS FROM ST. FRANCIS
ARE WAITING FOR US!

25:25.480 --> 25:27.917
HO, HO, HO!

25:35.838 --> 25:37.666
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

25:41.496 --> 25:43.280
-[MISCHIEVOUS MUSIC]

26:00.994 --> 26:03.649
-HEY, WHAT YOU WRAPPING THERE?

26:03.779 --> 26:06.303
-IT'S A GIFT...FOR MY MOM.

26:06.913 --> 26:08.610
-SPEAKING OF YOUR
MOM, ISN'T IT ABOUT

26:08.741 --> 26:10.003
TIME SHE PICKED YOU UP?

26:10.612 --> 26:12.222
-WELL, SHE HAD A
BIT OF A PROBLEM

26:12.353 --> 26:14.007
AND CAN'T MAKE IT 'TIL TOMORROW.

26:14.660 --> 26:16.270
SHE'D REALLY APPRECIATE IT
IF I COULD STAY ONE MORE

26:16.400 --> 26:19.490
NIGHT WITH YOU, BEING
CHRISTMAS TIME AND ALL.

26:19.621 --> 26:21.971
-OH, YOU TALKED TO
HER ON THE PHONE.

26:23.494 --> 26:24.713
BUT I WON'T BE
ABLE TO REACH HER.

26:26.715 --> 26:28.456
SHE'S STILL ON THE BUS.

26:33.679 --> 26:36.333
-HEY, DAD, COME ON, LET'S
GO SEE THE ST. FRANCIS KIDS.

26:36.464 --> 26:37.726
-OKAY, SEE YA

26:40.250 --> 26:41.730
-HOBIE: COME ON, THIS
IS REALLY COOL, HURRY UP.

26:42.252 --> 26:43.384
-MITCH: OKAY PAL, OKAY.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.190
-C.J.: WE NEED A LIFEGUARD
TO KEEP US SAFE.

27:10.106 --> 27:12.631
-YOU'VE GOT SUCH PASSION
FOR YOUR WORK, I ENVY YOU.

27:13.501 --> 27:15.285
-I CAN'T IMAGINE
DOING ANYTHING ELSE.

27:16.156 --> 27:18.549
MY MOM SAID I WAS BORN WITH
A RESCUE KIT IN MY HAND.

27:19.855 --> 27:20.813
-THE CHILDREN LOVE YOU.

27:26.775 --> 27:27.950
IT'S EASY TO SEE WHY.

27:34.653 --> 27:36.742
-[CHOKING]

27:48.754 --> 27:49.711
-OH NO.

27:53.323 --> 27:54.324
-STAY HERE!

27:55.848 --> 27:58.154
-[EXCITED CHATTER]

28:29.751 --> 28:30.665
-WHERE IS HE?

28:41.023 --> 28:45.027
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

29:17.451 --> 29:19.366
-HIS FRIEND SAID HE
INHALED A PIECE OF CANDY!

29:21.063 --> 29:22.064
-PRESSURE ON THE STOMACH.

29:23.109 --> 29:24.197
[GRUNTS]

29:27.896 --> 29:28.854
PUT HIM DOWN.

29:30.333 --> 29:31.726
OKAY, OKAY.

29:35.077 --> 29:36.078
NO PULSE!

29:36.818 --> 29:39.778
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:41.301 --> 29:43.869
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:44.739 --> 29:47.742
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR, FIVE.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.876
-THERE IT GOES, OKAY.

29:52.268 --> 29:54.227
YOU ALL RIGHT?
-KID: YEAH.

29:59.536 --> 30:03.889
-[MISCHIEVOUS CHATTER]

30:19.252 --> 30:20.470
-DEBBIE: NOW, PLEASE, GO!

30:26.346 --> 30:27.695
-HEY, GUYS!
-HEY, MATT.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.132
-HEY, MATT, SAW THAT
RESCUE! GOOD JOB!

30:30.263 --> 30:31.568
-GREAT, THANKS.

30:32.308 --> 30:33.919
-[SWEET MUSIC]

31:20.530 --> 31:21.836
-IS THIS THE COUNTY JAIL?

31:22.924 --> 31:24.273
KYLA JENNINGS, PLEASE.

31:26.362 --> 31:28.843
BUT I NEED TO TALK TO
HER, I'M HER DAUGHTER!

31:30.758 --> 31:31.759
-GUARD: KEEP IT SHORT.

31:33.500 --> 31:34.327
-HELLO

31:34.457 --> 31:35.676
-MOM, ARE YOU THERE?

31:36.633 --> 31:38.070
I'VE CALLED EVERYWHERE!

31:38.200 --> 31:39.767
THIS WAS MY LAST HOPE!

31:39.898 --> 31:42.422
-OH BABY, ARE YOU
OKAY? I MISS YOU.

31:42.552 --> 31:45.642
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME, MOM.
I'M GONNA BAIL YOU OUT.

31:46.774 --> 31:48.515
-DO YOU HAVE THE MONEY?

31:48.645 --> 31:51.779
-IT'S IN A SAFE PLACE. I'M
GONNA GO AND GET IT RIGHT NOW.

31:53.128 --> 31:54.086
I LOVE YOU, MOM.

31:54.216 --> 31:55.870
-OH, BABY, I LOVE YOU TOO.

31:56.958 --> 31:58.917
-SEE YOU SOON. BYE.

32:02.616 --> 32:03.922
-GUARD: COME ON, LET'S GO.

32:08.013 --> 32:09.101
-OH NO!

32:30.949 --> 32:32.733
-HEY, HEY, HEY, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:32.863 --> 32:35.127
YOU GOTTA WAIT 'TIL CHRISTMAS
LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE,

32:35.257 --> 32:37.346
WHETHER YOU BELIEVE
IN SANTA CLAUS OR NOT.

32:37.477 --> 32:38.826
COME ON, LET'S PLAY
WITH THE OTHER KIDS.

32:54.668 --> 32:56.496
-JOEY: I NEED TO
MAKE SOME MONEY FAST.

32:58.063 --> 32:59.890
FOR CHRISTMAS
PRESENTS, OF COURSE.

33:00.500 --> 33:03.329
-YEAH, ME TOO,
ESPECIALLY AFTER LOSING MY

33:03.459 --> 33:05.505
ALLOWANCE TO YOU LAST
NIGHT IN THAT POKER GAME.

33:17.865 --> 33:20.650
-HEY, HOBIE, HOW WOULD YOU
LIE TO MAKE SOME BIG MONEY?

33:20.781 --> 33:22.435
-NOT IF IT'S PLAYING
POKER WITH YOU.

33:22.565 --> 33:23.479
-IT'S NOT.

33:24.176 --> 33:26.700
ALL WE NEED IS A
PICTURE OF YOUR DAD.

33:31.487 --> 33:32.793
-MY DAD?

33:37.972 --> 33:39.800
-SO YOU GET THE CHANCE
TO BE AN HONORARY

33:39.930 --> 33:41.889
LIFEGUARD IN THE NEW
YEAR'S PARADE WITH

33:42.020 --> 33:43.717
THIS HANDSOME
LIFEGUARD RIGHT HERE.

33:44.239 --> 33:46.937
-ALL YOU HAVE TO
DO IS DONATE $20

33:47.068 --> 33:48.591
THAT GOES TOWARDS THE
FLOAT FOR THE PARADE

33:48.722 --> 33:50.898
AND HE'LL MAKE HIS
CHOICE IN A FEW DAYS.

33:51.029 --> 33:53.031
-WELL, YEAH, I'M IN!
-OKAY.

33:54.075 --> 33:56.338
-GREAT, THANKS, HOPE TO
SEE YOU GUYS AT THE PARADE.

33:57.600 --> 33:59.472
-[JAZZ MUSIC]

34:10.351 --> 34:13.703
♪ TIS THE SEASON JOY WERE BRINGING

34:14.356 --> 34:17.664
♪ IT'S THAT SPECIAL TIME OF YEAR ♪

34:18.491 --> 34:22.147
♪ SLEIGH BELLS RINGING CAROLERS SINGING ♪

34:22.277 --> 34:25.715
♪ FOR ALL THE WORLD TO HEAR

34:26.498 --> 34:27.413
♪ IT'S THAT TIME

34:27.543 --> 34:29.806
♪ WHEN YOUR IN MY ARMS

34:29.937 --> 34:33.245
♪ OOH FEELS SO GOOD

34:33.375 --> 34:36.465
♪ IT'S CHRISTMAS CHRISTMAS TIME

34:36.596 --> 34:38.902
♪ WHEN I'M NEXT TO YOU

34:40.687 --> 34:42.949
♪ I'M NEXT TO YOU

34:44.777 --> 34:46.954
♪ WHEN I'M NEXT TO YOU

34:48.824 --> 34:51.610
♪ IT'S CHRISTMAS TIME

34:52.829 --> 34:55.179
♪ IT'S CHRISTMAS TIME

34:59.793 --> 35:00.968
-YEAH, HAVE YOU SEEN HOBIE?

35:01.925 --> 35:04.885
ALL RIGHT, IF HE SHOWS UP, HAVE
HIM CALL ME AT HEADQUARTERS.

35:05.451 --> 35:06.278
THANK YOU.

35:07.496 --> 35:08.323
DAMMIT.

35:11.109 --> 35:12.936
-HEY, HEY, HEY!
MERRY CHRISTMAS!

35:13.067 --> 35:14.938
-YEAH, HO, HO, HO.

35:15.983 --> 35:17.158
-WHAT? TROUBLE IN PARADISE?

35:17.289 --> 35:18.725
I DON'T KNOW WHAT BUGS ME MORE,

35:18.855 --> 35:20.814
THE FACT THAT HOBIE AND
JOEY ARE AN HOUR LATE

35:20.944 --> 35:22.424
OR THERE'S STILL NO
SIGN OF HER MOTHER.

35:22.555 --> 35:24.296
-WELL, SOUNDS LIKE A TIE TO ME.

35:26.080 --> 35:27.037
-YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE!

35:27.690 --> 35:28.735
-UH, I DIDN'T.

35:30.867 --> 35:33.609
-WE ONLY HAVE $300.
IT'S NOT ENOUGH.

35:34.262 --> 35:36.438
-JOEY, EVERYONE'S GONE
HOME, BESIDES, MY DAD'S

35:36.569 --> 35:38.353
ALREADY GONNA KILL
US FOR BEING LATE.

35:38.484 --> 35:41.530
-HEY, KID, COME HERE, I NEED
TO TALK TO YOU, COME HERE!

35:41.661 --> 35:43.315
-JOEY: OH NO! HE'S AFTER ME!

35:44.229 --> 35:45.143
-JOEY, RUN!

35:45.882 --> 35:47.232
-I DON'T THINK SO!

35:50.191 --> 35:51.323
LET'S TALK ABOUT
YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

35:51.453 --> 35:52.498
-I DON'T THINK SO!

36:03.596 --> 36:04.423
-NOW I'M PISSED.

36:07.426 --> 36:08.253
-JOEY!

36:17.436 --> 36:19.960
-JOEY, YOU OKAY? WHERE ARE YOU?

36:20.526 --> 36:22.005
-HOBIE, I'M OVER HERE!

36:25.400 --> 36:29.926
-HOBIE: YOU OKAY?
-LOOK, I DON'T WANNA
HURT NO KIDS, UNDERSTAND?

36:30.057 --> 36:32.190
-HOBIE: UP HERE.
-TONY: I JUST WANT THE MONEY!

36:35.280 --> 36:36.498
-HOBIE: ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

36:42.765 --> 36:43.940
JOEY, COME ON, THIS WAY.

36:45.725 --> 36:46.726
-TONY: THAT'S REAL BRIGHT.

36:48.293 --> 36:49.859
-HOBIE: ALL RIGHT,
WATCH YOUR HEAD.

36:54.342 --> 36:56.518
-LIKE I'M NOT GONNA
FIND YOU UP HERE? HUH?

37:03.482 --> 37:05.135
-[LAUGHS] HEY!

37:09.183 --> 37:10.315
[YELLS]

37:19.498 --> 37:21.587
-HOBIE! I'M SCARED!

37:21.717 --> 37:23.110
-IT'S OKAY, JUST
DON'T LOOK DOWN.

37:35.818 --> 37:37.429
-[LAUGHS]

37:48.614 --> 37:49.919
-HOBIE: I HEAR HIM COMING!

37:54.794 --> 37:56.317
COME ON, WE HAVE TO KEEP GOING!

37:56.448 --> 37:58.276
-HOBIE, I CAN'T MOVE!

37:58.406 --> 38:00.147
-DON'T WORRY, I'VE GOT YOU!

38:01.844 --> 38:04.934
HE'S CATCHING UP!
WATCH YOUR HEAD!

38:12.115 --> 38:13.813
-ANY WORD ON HOBIE?

38:13.943 --> 38:15.293
-J.B. HASN'T SEEN HIM ALL
DAY AND NEITHER HAS CONNER.

38:15.423 --> 38:16.772
-THEY'RE NOT AT
LANDON'S EITHER.

38:17.730 --> 38:19.514
-I'M BEYOND MAD
NOW, I'M WORRIED.

38:19.645 --> 38:21.255
-WELL, LET'S JUST
HOPE FOR THE BEST.

38:21.386 --> 38:23.213
-THANKS.
-MITCH, I JUST GOT
A CALL FROM A WORKER

38:23.344 --> 38:24.911
ON THE SANTA MONICA PIER.

38:25.912 --> 38:28.131
TWO KIDS ARE TRAPPED UNDER
THE PIER ON THE CATWALK.

38:28.262 --> 38:30.482
-DAMN IT! I KNEW IT! LET'S GO.

38:44.452 --> 38:45.497
-TONY: HERE I COME!

38:57.465 --> 38:59.075
NO PLACE TO RUN, BABY!

39:00.642 --> 39:01.687
-JOEY, FASTER!

39:03.602 --> 39:04.864
-NO PLACE TO HIDE!

39:18.312 --> 39:20.445
MAKE IT EASY ON YOURSELF, KID.

39:23.883 --> 39:25.537
JUST WANT THE MONEY, KIDS!

39:37.766 --> 39:40.247
[LAUGHS]

39:55.915 --> 39:57.264
-[SCREAMS]

40:02.138 --> 40:04.750
-JOEY! JOEY, HANG ON! HERE!

40:07.796 --> 40:08.623
-HOBIE!

40:08.754 --> 40:09.972
-JOEY!

40:10.103 --> 40:11.713
-HOBIE, I CAN'T HANG ON!

40:13.193 --> 40:14.368
-GIVE ME YOUR OTHER HAND!

40:14.499 --> 40:15.717
-I'M SLIPPING!

40:15.848 --> 40:17.415
-JOEY, GIVE ME YOUR OTHER HAND!

40:24.987 --> 40:26.119
DON'T LOOK DOWN!

40:36.999 --> 40:38.566
-HOBIE! HOBIE!

40:43.484 --> 40:46.444
-[SCREAMS]
-JOEY! NO!

40:49.795 --> 40:50.709
NO!

41:09.945 --> 41:12.426
-[ENDING THEME MUSIC]
